India Group May Bid for BHP South Africa Coal Rights, WSJ Says

-- B y   J o h n   C h a c k o
-- 
2011-02-11T07:56:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/india-group-may-bid-for-bhp-south-africa-coal-rights-wsj-says.html
International Coal Ventures Ltd., a
grouping of Indian state-run metal and energy companies, may bid
for  BHP Billiton Ltd .’s coal prospecting rights in South Africa,
the Wall Street Journal reported.  The company is collecting information about the properties
of BHP’s unit based in the Mpumalanga region, according to the
report, which cited C.S. Verma, Chairman of Steel Authority of
India, one of the partners in ICVL.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Chacko at 
 jchacko@bloomberg.net  